    "narrative": "For LawDog on April 9th, 2026, the lineup construction is dictated by a lack of elite high-ceiling matchups, leaving **Gleyber Torres** as the premier start of the day with a score of 51.30. **Gleyber Torres** benefits significantly from his #2 spot in the order, which provides a +8% efficiency boost, neutralizing the negative impact of his platoon disadvantage against the right-handed Abel. While the SP_xERA of 4.28 for the opposing pitcher is relatively neutral, **Gleyber Torres** possesses the best combination of lineup protection and park factors currently available to us. Conversely, **Geraldo Perdomo** struggles to break into the \"Strong\" tier, landing at 41.97 due to a poor matchup against McLean, whose 3.04 xERA acts as a significant drag on our efficiency goals.\n\nThe most difficult decision was the exclusion of **Lawrence Butler**, who represents the \"closest miss\" of the day. Despite a solid base projection of 54.42, **Lawrence Butler** was ultimately benched due to a projected #5 order placement and a negative dynamic platoon adjustment against the left-handed Weathers. His exclusion reflects our organizational priority of optimizing for high-leverage lineup positions; with **Gavin Sheets** also operating at a marginal 45.53 efficiency, we are essentially treading water today. We are clearly feeling the absence of **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, **Cal Raleigh**, and **Will Smith**, whose collective team off-day prevents us from chasing the stolen base or power upside we desperately need to climb the 5x5 standings. Keep a close eye on the late-afternoon weather reports, but for now, we are deploying this trio of **Gleyber Torres**, **Geraldo Perdomo**, and **Gavin Sheets** with the intent of maintaining our game caps while awaiting more favorable conditions for the rest of our roster.",
